# Human-readable reference only — not read by Alchemy CLI for all keys; use real `.env.local` / `.env.staging` / `.env.production` (gitignored).
# Local dev: `bun run dev` (Turbo runs `alchemy dev --app <id>` for the web + each deployable worker package; see root README).
# Deploy (full monorepo graph): `bun run deploy:prod` · `deploy:staging` · `deploy:preview` — see https://alchemy.run/getting-started/ and https://alchemy.run/concepts/state/
# Every `alchemy.run.ts` reads **`process.env.STAGE`** (`local` via dev scripts, `prod` / `staging` / `pr-<n>` for deploy).

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Local — repo-root `.env.local`
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Cloudflare — optional locally if you use `bunx wrangler login` / `bun alchemy login`. Required for many deploy/CI flows.
# IMPORTANT: TOKEN and ACCOUNT_ID must be from the SAME account — mixing accounts or pasting values into the wrong vars causes confusing failures (wrong workers.dev host, `[CloudflareStateStore]` POST 404 + text/html).
# CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN=
# CLOUDFLARE_ACCOUNT_ID=

# Alchemy — Cloud-backed deploy state token (same value for every CI deploy / machine on one Cloudflare account). See https://alchemy.run/guides/cloudflare-state-store/
# Generate: openssl rand -base64 32
# Required on GitHub staging + production Environments (`github:sync:*`) and locally in `.env.staging` / `.env.production` for sync — not needed for `.env.local` unless you intentionally set CI=true.
# ALCHEMY_STATE_TOKEN=

# Alchemy — required. Encrypts `alchemy.secret()` in state (see https://alchemy.run/concepts/secret/#encryption-password)
# Same value everywhere `alchemy deploy` runs for that stage: `.env.staging` / `.env.production`, GitHub Actions, other CI — not different passwords per machine.
# Set in `.env.local` (run `bun run setup`) or staging/prod dotfiles (`bun run setup:staging` / `bun run setup:prod`).
# Use a strong, stable value in production, CI, and any shared or long-lived state.
# ALCHEMY_PASSWORD=

# Secret binding example — required. Shared by the web worker and chatroom worker.
# The browser never receives this value; the web worker uses it when forwarding `/api/ws/*` to the chatroom DO.
# CHATROOM_INTERNAL_SECRET=

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Staging + PR previews — repo-root `.env.staging` (gitignored)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Used by `bun run deploy:staging` (`STAGE=staging`) and PR preview deploys in CI (`STAGE=pr-<n>`, same file).
# Same keys as production where applicable. Create with `bun run setup:staging`.
# Preview deploys (**`STAGE=pr-*`**) ignore **`WEB_*`** — the web app stays on workers.dev only for PR stacks.

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Production — repo-root `.env.production` (optional if you only pass env in CI)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Used by `bun run deploy:prod` (`STAGE=prod`). Create with `bun run setup:prod`.
# Same Cloudflare vars as needed for `alchemy deploy`. Include **`ALCHEMY_STATE_TOKEN`** (see above) before `github:sync:prod`.

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Web Worker — custom domains / routes (optional, staging + production dotfiles only)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Configure via `bun run setup:staging` / `bun run setup:prod` (bottom of menu) or edit the dotfile.
# Omit or leave commented → deploy stays on **`workers.dev`** only (`apps/web/alchemy.run.ts`).
# **`github:sync:*`** pushes these as GitHub Environment **variables** when non-empty — CI workflows pass them to `alchemy deploy`.
#
# Comma-separated hostnames (typical): `example.com,www.example.com`
# WEB_DOMAINS=
# Comma-separated route patterns (escape hatch): `example.com/*` — use when you need explicit route patterns
# WEB_ROUTES=
# Optional — applied to every WEB_DOMAINS / WEB_ROUTES entry when set
# WEB_ZONE_ID=
# Optional — `true` / `false` / `yes` / `1` · only when replacing a hostname already bound to another Worker
# WEB_DOMAIN_OVERRIDE_EXISTING_ORIGIN=

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# GitHub Actions deploy enablement (Environment variable, not a dotenv key)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Set **`CF_STARTER_DEPLOY_ENABLED=true`** on GitHub Environments **`staging`** and **`production`** so deploy workflows run.
# Fresh forks: workflows no-op successfully until this is set. See `bun run github:setup`.

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Admin stack — local-only sync to GitHub (`bun run github:sync:staging` / `bun run github:sync:prod`)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Do not run from normal CI/deploy. Run from a trusted dev/admin machine. Sync writes GitHub Environment *secrets*:
# `ALCHEMY_PASSWORD`, `ALCHEMY_STATE_TOKEN`, `CHATROOM_INTERNAL_SECRET`, `CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN` — and *variables* (plaintext on the Environment):
# `CLOUDFLARE_ACCOUNT_ID` (prefer as a GitHub Variable, not a Secret—it is metadata), `CF_STARTER_DEPLOY_ENABLED` (defaults to true on sync if omitted in the dotfile),
# and optional **`WEB_DOMAINS`**, **`WEB_ROUTES`**, **`WEB_ZONE_ID`**, **`WEB_DOMAIN_OVERRIDE_EXISTING_ORIGIN`** when set in the same dotfile (see section above).
# Defaults to the current `gh auth token` and `gh repo view` when these are omitted.
# If set manually, GITHUB_TOKEN needs repo scope for private repos, or public_repo for public repos.
# GITHUB_TOKEN=
# GITHUB_REPOSITORY=owner/repo
# Optional overrides:
# GITHUB_OWNER=
# GITHUB_REPOSITORY_NAME=
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# GitHub admin sync — `GITHUB_SYNC_SCOPE` (required by stacks/admin.ts)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# **`bun run github:sync:*`** / **`bun run github:sync`** set `GITHUB_SYNC_SCOPE=secrets` via package.json (do not rely on implicit defaults).
# **`bun run github:env:*`** / **`bun run github:env`** set `GITHUB_SYNC_SCOPE=environment` — no dotfile; requires:
#   GITHUB_SYNC_ENVIRONMENT_ONLY_CONFIRM=true
#   and every **`GITHUB_ENV_*`** key below (empty string = none).
#
# To update deployment protection **during** a secrets sync, set for that run:
#   GITHUB_SYNC_UPDATE_ENVIRONMENT_PROTECTION=true
#   plus the same full **`GITHUB_ENV_*`** set.
#
# GITHUB_SYNC_SCOPE=secrets
# GITHUB_SYNC_UPDATE_ENVIRONMENT_PROTECTION=false
# GITHUB_SYNC_ENVIRONMENT_ONLY_CONFIRM=
#
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# GitHub Environment deployment protection — all required when using env-only sync or UPDATE_ENVIRONMENT_PROTECTION
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# GITHUB_ENV_WAIT_TIMER_MINUTES=0
# GITHUB_ENV_PREVENT_SELF_REVIEW=false
# GITHUB_ENV_DEPLOYMENT_BRANCH_PROTECTED_ONLY=false
# GITHUB_ENV_DEPLOYMENT_REVIEWER_USERS=alice,bob
# GITHUB_ENV_DEPLOYMENT_REVIEWER_TEAMS=
# GITHUB_ENV_DEPLOYMENT_BRANCH_CUSTOM_PATTERNS=
